x
y
x\in N(\mu_x, \sigma_x^2), y\in N(\mu_y, \sigma_y^2)
e^{ix} + e^{iy}
 \mathbb{E} \arg (e^{ix} + e^{iy}) 
e^{ix} + e^{iy} = cos(x) + cos(y) + i[sin(x) + sin(y)]
\arg e^{ix} + e^{iy} = tan^{-1} \frac{sin(x) +sin(y)}{cos(x) + cos(y)}=tan^{-1}tan((x+y)/2) = (x + y)/2
\arg e^{ix_1} + \dots  + e^{ix_N}
